DURBAN - Two women were the victims of a shooting in Phoenix. A 70-year-old and 30-year-old woman were shot in their home in Redberry, Phoenix in the early hours of Wednesday morning. “At approximately 2.51 am, members of  Reaction Unit South Africa (Rusa) were dispatched to the scene after receiving reports from the public on the shooting. Upon arrival a 70-year-old woman was found to have sustained a single gunshot wound to her hand and a 30-year-old woman was shot in the thigh,” said Prem Balram, Rusa spokesperson. The women were stabilised at the scene by paramedics from the Provincial Ambulance Service before being taken to hospital. Both victims told Rusa they heard someone break the glass of the sliding door. One gunman then entered their home and shot both women before picking up the spent cartridges and fleeing the scene without a word or stealing from the home. The reason behind the shooting is unknown. Daily News